 won't need reflection since it's a publicly inherited method. I'll keep in mind that casting will be suppressed, which is important. I might need to handle IOException and ClassNotFoundException because readObject throws these exceptions. It’s essential to ensure that my method can manage any potential errors that arise during serialization, keeping everything robust and smooth.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nTqFXvrfceDfRTWbBAQ49lbd|fc_05fd1b3986c3cb2e0169f440a82ea881938256918f239c0bf3", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cn.hutool/hutool-all/5.8.25/src/test/java/cn_hutool/hutool_all/ValidateObjectInputStreamTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage cn_hutool.hutool_all;\n\nimport cn.hutool.core.io.ValidateObjectInputStream;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ValidateObjectInputStreamTest {\n    @Test\n    public void resolvesAcceptedClassWhenReadingSerializedObject() throws Exception {\n        ArrayList<String> expected = new ArrayList<>(List.of(\"alpha\", \"beta\"));\n        byte[] serialized = serialize(expected);\n\n        try (ValidateObjectInputStream inputStream = new ValidateObjectInputStream(\n                new ByteArrayInputStream(serialized), ArrayList.class)) {\n            Object restored = inputStream.readObject();\n\n            assertThat(restored).isInstanceOf(ArrayList.class);\n            assertThat((ArrayList<String>) restored).containsExactly(\"alpha\", \"beta\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] serialize(Object value) throws IOException {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream = new ObjectOutputStream(outputStream)) {\n            objectOutputStream.writeObject(value);\n        }\n        return outputStream.toByteArray();\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2424, "output": 945, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37161, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777615002291, "responseId": "resp_05fd1b3986c3cb2e0169f4409abdcc8193973f392d93f3d392"}}
